  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CIR Administration and Financial Management Capacity Building and Support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Approval 1 (2015): In 2013 and 2015 an external assessment by Vetor of CIR&apos;s financial management and systems revealed a number of weaknesses and inconsistencies, and at CIR&apos;s request, a capacity building and verification of expenses programme was defined in two stages: December 2015 and January 2016, funded by the Norwegian Embassy and CAFOD respectively. The first stage is now complete, revealing serious concerns on financial mismanagement of 2014 funds, and this second phase is to complete a verification of 2015 expenses and financial capacity strengthening with CIR&apos;s coordination team, Board, indigenous leaders and audit committee. 

Approval 2 (2016): As a result of the above exercise, and an accredited audit (BRA558 - reports due 16/3/16) it was highlighted that a number of payments were made by CIR in 2014 and 2015 without due justifications. In addition, a number of organisational problems were highlighted: the lack of technical capacity of CIR&apos;s staff, the inadequacy of financial reporting and the institution&apos;s internal controls, the lack of standards and resource management procedures, and disorganisation of the records and documents. Currently the Administrative and Financial department (AFD) lacks efficiency and effectiveness in managing their resources. This consultancy aims to support the restructuring of CIR&apos;s AFD over the course of 2016, in collaboration with the Norwegian Embassy and Ford Foundation, with a view to re-commence CAFOD&apos;s partnership with CIR.

Approval 3 (2016): this approval relates to the last tranche of the payments due to the consultant for the verification of CIR 2015 expenses and Financial Management Capacity building work. We have now received the final reports.

Approval 4-5 (2017-2019): in light of the mismanagement (fraud case) of CIR finances, it was agreed between the Norwegian Embassy, Ford Foundation and CAFOD that each agency would support CIR to rebuild and strengthen their Administration and Financial capacity in the view to continue their valuable work and our partnership with them. The cost and management of the consultant&apos;s work is being split equality between the three agencies from 2017 to 2019.</narrative>
  </description>
